author: COMSOL
description: This example simulates the thermodynamical evolution of moist air in an electronic box with the aim of detecting whether condensation occurs when the external environment properties change. The model imports measured data for the air temperature, pressure, and water vapor concentration. The water vapor concentration is considered to be homogeneous inside the box and equal to the external concentration.
